org.matsim.core.router.util

Interface LinkToLinkTravelTime

  • All Known Implementing Classes:
    FreespeedTravelTimeAndDisutility

    public interface LinkToLinkTravelTime
    Interface for travel time queries that include the link travel time and the time needed for the turning move.
    Author:
    dgrether

    • Method Summary

      All Methods Instance Methods Abstract Methods 
      Modifier and Type Method and Description
      double getLinkToLinkTravelTime(Link fromLink, Link toLink, double time)
      Returns the travel time at the specified time for the given fromLink inclusive the turning move time to enter the given toLink.

    • Method Detail

      • getLinkToLinkTravelTime

        double getLinkToLinkTravelTime(Link fromLink,
                               Link toLink,
                               double time)
        Returns the travel time at the specified time for the given fromLink inclusive the turning move time to enter the given toLink.
        Parameters:
        fromLink - The link for which the travel time is calculated.
        toLink - The link that is entered from the fromLink the turning move time is calculated for the fromLink toLink relationship.
        time - The departure time (in seconds since 00:00) at the beginning of the fromLink for which the travel time is calculated.
        Returns:
        The time (in seconds) needed to travel over the fromLink fromLink and enter the toLink toLink, departing at time time.
